{"id":87337,"title":"Treatment of tar burns: two case reports.","abstract":"Hot tar burns are still a challenging clinical form because the removal of tar is very difficult for the emergency physician and there is no specified appropriate agent for the removal of tar. In this study, two patients with hot tar burns who were treated with diesel, sunflower oil and mayonnaise are presented.","date":"2014-09-25","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25252526","annotations":[{"name":"Physician","weight":0.317786,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician"},{"name":"Burn","weight":0.201782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burn"},{"name":"Emergency","weight":0.17344,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency"},{"name":"Tar","weight":0.125146,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tar"},{"name":"Oil","weight":0.106826,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oil"},{"name":"Diesel fuel","weight":0.0499462,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diesel_fuel"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Mayonnaise","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayonnaise"},{"name":"Emergency physician","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency_physician"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.029746,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Sunflower","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunflower"},{"name":"Sunflower oil","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunflower_oil"},{"name":"Case report","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Case_report"},{"name":"Law of agency","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_of_agency"}]}
